<br>
I was under my main, a Cleric, in Sebilis.  My tank and I zone in and get a great group of 5 together.  He was our Shaman.  We proceed to take the zone out in Seb ... doing great ... had a wipe.<br>
<br>
Well, we get back in there and I finally rez everyone, myself last of course, and sit to med.  A 60 Ranger by the name of Dymonds (?) comes over  (mind you, us casters are oom!) yelling for help.  I manage to get a heal off on her and help her out.  Next thing I know she pulls more (at the behest of this Shaman I believe) and comes back and yells for help again.<br>
<br>
Ok, so we invited her into this group thinking they would both be great additions.<br>
<br>
WRONG!<br>
<br>
Still trying to med (10 mana at this point in time) this Ranger keeps pulling .. and pulling .. and pulling, not listening to the OOM message I am giving.  Shaman, does nothing.  She dies.  Luckily my tank lived!  Well, so did everyone else.  Come to find out this Ranger was his real life cousin.  He stands up, drags her corpse and proceeds to go &quot;linkdead&quot; at the entrance of Sebilis, leaving us with a group of 4 at the zone out and nothing but threats and nasty comments from this Ranger.<br>
<br>
He never healed.  He rarely slowed.  He didn't believe in DoT's.  I don't know where his mana went, but he sure never used it with us!<br>
<br>
I hope this helps out some.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
